OL,3,CInfected blood: 'Chilling' cover-up of
OL,4,Cscandal that was 'no accident'
OL,6,FITV Political Correspondent Harry
OL,7,FHorton breaks down the key findings
OL,8,Ffrom the report.
OL,10,FThe infected blood scandal which
OL,11,Fclaimed thousands of lives was "no
OL,12,Faccident", the inquiry into the
OL,13,Fdisaster has concluded.
OL,15,FLabelled the "worst treatment disaster
OL,16,Fin the NHS," the saw more than 30,000
OL,17,Fpeople infected with HIV and Hepatitis
OL,18,FC after being treated with
OL,19,Fcontaminated blood products.
