OL,6,F"Standing back, and viewing the
OL,7,Fresponse of the NHS and of government
OL,8,Foverall, the answer to the question
OL,9,F'was there a cover-up?' is that there
OL,10,Fhas been", Sir Brian said.
OL,12,F"Not in the sense of a handful of
OL,13,Fpeople plotting in an orchestrated
OL,14,Fconspiracy to mislead, but in a way
OL,15,Fthat was more subtle, more pervasive
OL,16,Fand more chilling in its implications.
OL,18,F"In this way there has been a hiding
OL,19,Fof much of the truth."
