OL,6,FIn total, more than 3,000 people are
OL,7,Fknown to have died as a result of the
OL,8,Finfected blood scandal. The
OL,9,FHaemophilia Society also estimates
OL,10,Fbetween the start of the inquiry and
OL,11,Fthe publishing of its findings,
OL,12,Fanother 650 will have also passed away.
OL,14,FCampaign group Factor 8 say one victim
OL,15,Fdies every four days. There are also
OL,16,Fan estimated 98 deaths since the
OL,17,Finquiry recommended everyone get
OL,18,Fimmediate compensation last April.
