OL,6,FThe blood donated was then pooled
OL,7,Ftogether to make the drugs, which
OL,8,Fmeant entire batches were often
OL,9,Fcontaminated.
OL,11,FThere were numerous warnings about the
OL,12,Fimported blood and the risks, but the
OL,13,FUK was unable to produce the amounts
OL,14,Fof blood it needed, so carried on
OL,15,Fimporting it from abroad.
OL,17,FOne shocking case saw boys with
OL,18,Fhaeomophilia tested on with the
OL,19,Fproducts without their knowledge.
OL,1,Wz5~k4~k7}hw1 ~k4~sj5j5~s1 G    G16/21
